See the following wiki site for instructions on installation and configuration.
https://sites.google.com/a/seagate.com/sspl/

To build the RPMs do the following:
    cd into the desired low-level or high-level directory
    Execute build_rpm.bsh
    The RPM will be at the same level and named: SSPL-LL-x.y.z-a.el7.noarch.rpm

Note: The RPM build requires the rpm-build package to be installed:
    yum install rpm-build

